cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper explicitly discusses the computational complexity of the game and provides complexity results for different parameters. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper analyzes the algorithmic aspects of the game and proposes efficient algorithms for solving it under certain conditions. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper introduces several two-player versions of the game and analyzes their complexity. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper may be of interest to researchers working on game AI, as the Buttons & Scissors game can be seen as a simple game that requires strategic thinking. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The paper discusses restrictions on the board size, cut directions, and cut sizes, which are related to geometric properties of the game.
